-- Mexico Stocks: Asur, Homex, Geo, Industrias Penoles Are Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-04-04T19:03:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/mexico-stocks-asur-homex-geo-industrias-penoles-are-active.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of 1:20 p.m. in Mexico City.  The IPC  index  fell 1.2 percent to 39,448.61.  Mexican homebuilders were among the biggest losers as the
country’s equities followed U.S. stocks lower. Minutes of the
 Federal Reserve ’s March 13 meeting released yesterday showed the
central bankers may refrain from boosting monetary stimulus.
Mexico sends about 80 percent of its exports to the U.S.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX*)  , Mexico’s largest
homebuilder by revenue, slipped 1.9 percent to 38.40 pesos.
Corp. Geo SAB (GEOB MM), Mexico’s second-largest homebuilder,
dropped 2.3 percent to 19.50 pesos.  Grupo Aeroportuario del Sureste SAB  (ASURB MM), the
operator of airports in southern Mexico, rose 0.4 percent to
92.01 pesos. Asur’s passenger traffic climbed 9.1 percent in
March from a year earlier, according to a statement to the
Mexican stock exchange today.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES*)  (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer and a miner of gold, dropped 3.2 percent to
614.45 pesos. Gold fell to a 12-week low in  New York , and silver
retreated the most in five weeks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
